				 NMDC plans three pellet plants

 A STAFF REPORTER
																								Calcutta, Dec. 7: The National Mineral Development Corporation (NMDC) plans to invest Rs 2,000 crore to set up three pellet plants in the country.
																								The state-run firm has joined hands with RINL for a plant in Chhattisgarh at an investment of Rs 1,244 crore.
																								The fine ore of Bailadila will be the main feed of the plant. A detailed draft feasibility report has been prepared.
																								The NMDC also proposes to set up a 1-million-tonne pellet plant at Donimalai. The estimated investment here is in the range of Rs 300-350 crore. 
																								Another pellet plant with a capacity of 1 million tonnes per annum is being planned to better utilise the slimes at Bailadila. The estimated project cost is around Rs 350 crore. 
																								The NMDC has paid a 100 per cent interim dividend recently. So far, it has paid a total dividend of Rs 1,410 crore to the Centre. NMDC chairman Rana Som handed over the cheque of Rs 130 crore to steel minister Ram Vilas Paswan.

